Tom Dier:  Good to hear your sage wisdom.<br><br>
I question your statement about draftees vs. volunteers and the resultant anger.  There could be something there!  I didn't have any choice about where the Army sent me... even though I was a career soldier.  Maybe I was indoctrinated more than the average draftee.  I, too, loved the Vietnamese people... and I hated them... the beginning of the Ping Pong ball effect.  Depersonalization worked for me... just long enough to get in way over my head.. it doesn't work today.<br>
Is it an affordable luxury to ask &quot;Why and What for?&quot;...before you go... it is certainly a curse to ask &quot;Why and What for?&quot;.. after the fact.<br>
God, the epitome of freedom, certainly gave mankind the latitude to behave as fools.<br><br>
Best to you and your family, Tom<br><br>
Edward Ramon
